HEADWORD: Limbat
<hw>Lim"bat</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧m"b⟦acr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>A cooling periodical wind in the Isle of Cyprus,
blowing from the northwest from eight o'clock, <sc>A. M.</sc>, to the
middle of the day or later.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

